.TH "st_slim_rproc_alloc" 9 "st_slim_rproc_alloc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
st_slim_rproc_alloc \- allocate and initialise slim rproc
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct st_slim_rproc *" st_slim_rproc_alloc
.BI "(struct platform_device *pdev "  ","
.BI "char *fw_name "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
Pointer to the platform_device struct
.IP "fw_name" 12
Name of firmware for rproc to use
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Function for allocating and initialising a slim rproc for use by
device drivers whose IP is based around the SLIM core. It
obtains and enables any clocks required by the SLIM core and also
ioremaps the various IO.

Returns st_slim_rproc pointer or \fBPTR_ERR\fP on error.
